But, yeah, there's, there's gotta be 20 cars at the bottom.
但是 坑下面得有二十多辆车吧

344
00:19:01,970 --> 00:19:05,340
And some of the people in some of those cars, they ain't comin' back.
那些车里的人 永远上不来了

345
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:08,210
Jesus, I was, I was just there last night,
老天 我昨天下班就堵在那里

346
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:09,740
backed up in traffic.
堵在那好久

347
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:12,520
Thank God you weren't there this morning.
幸好你今早不在那里

348
00:19:12,540 --> 00:19:15,130
I assume you know about California.
听说加州的事了吧

349
00:19:15,150 --> 00:19:16,830
I didn't turn on the TV this morning.
我今早没看电视

350
00:19:16,850 --> 00:19:18,050
-Oh! -Is there something new?
-难怪 -有什么新闻吗？

351
00:19:18,070 --> 00:19:21,010
The, the rest of it went.
都沉下去了

352
00:19:21,030 --> 00:19:24,530
I-I mean, th-they're saying that 20% of Northern California is hanging in there,
电视说北加州20%还尚存

353
00:19:24,550 --> 00:19:26,320
which probably means, what, 10%?
实际也许还剩10%

354
00:19:26,340 --> 00:19:30,240
But the food-producing regions are... they're gone.
但是粮食产区都没了

355
00:19:30,430 --> 00:19:32,190
And with the Midwest turning to charcoal
中西部被烧成个焦土

356
00:19:32,210 --> 00:19:33,890
and Florida flooding, that's like
佛州又被水淹

357
00:19:33,910 --> 00:19:38,370
all the food-producing regions in the country just gone.
全国粮仓都没了

358
00:19:38,390 --> 00:19:39,770
And the same thing with Europe.
欧洲的情况也差不多

359
00:19:39,790 --> 00:19:41,330
I mean, it's famine time in Asia.
亚洲也在闹饥荒

360
00:19:41,350 --> 00:19:42,770
There's a million people dead.
听说那死了一百万人

361
00:19:42,790 --> 00:19:44,370
They're saying it's the bub-bublonic,
他们管它叫做 树 树疫

362
00:19:44,390 --> 00:19:45,600
-bubonic plague. -Bubonic.
-树疫病 -鼠疫

363
00:19:45,620 --> 00:19:47,560
Bu-Bubonic plague. Yeah.
对 鼠疫

364
00:19:47,580 --> 00:19:49,860
And the bees, I mean, they were in trouble a decade ago,
还有蜜蜂 十多年前就不正常

365
00:19:49,880 --> 00:19:51,340
but they're completely gone now.
但现在所有蜜蜂都没了

366
00:19:51,360 --> 00:19:54,040
I mean, there's a couple of hives or whatever down in South America,
也许南美洲还有几个蜂巢吧

367
00:19:54,060 --> 00:19:55,960
but there ain't no honey, honey.
但不产蜂蜜

368
00:19:55,980 --> 00:19:59,740
And without those little guys, like, what's gonna pollinate all the crops we have left?
没有这些小虫虫 怎么给剩下的庄稼授粉呢

369
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:00,790
I mean, I can't do...
要我说 我可...

370
00:20:00,810 --> 00:20:02,140
Excuse me. One sec.
先打住 稍后聊

371
00:20:02,160 --> 00:20:03,440
Yeah, yeah. That's-that's cool.
哦 哦 好

372
00:20:03,460 --> 00:20:05,310
A-Andrea? Are you,
是 安 安德莉娅吗？

373
00:20:05,330 --> 00:20:07,190
are you Andrea from Midwest Trust?
你是中西部信托银行的安德莉娅吗？

374
00:20:07,210 --> 00:20:09,230
I'm Felicia Anderson's husband.
我是菲莉西娅·安德森的丈夫

375
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:11,410
Ex, actually.
实际上 是前夫

376
00:20:11,430 --> 00:20:12,930
I think you and Fel know each other.
我觉得你和小菲互相认识

377
00:20:12,950 --> 00:20:14,720
We met at a, a, a game night at David's.
我们之前在大卫家聚会时见过

378
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:15,830
A few game nights.
几晚游戏聚会

379
00:20:15,850 --> 00:20:17,200
Yeah, sure.
对 记得

380
00:20:17,220 --> 00:20:18,810
What do you want?
你想干什么？

381
00:20:18,830 --> 00:20:21,070
I just had a long walk, and my car is stuck,
车堵在路上 我刚走了半天

382
00:20:21,090 --> 00:20:25,420
and the bank is, it's leaning.
而银行 斜了

383
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:26,830
Leaning?
斜了？

384
00:20:27,010 --> 00:20:28,240
Yeah.
是的

385
00:20:28,530 --> 00:20:31,240
It's on the edge of the sinkhole.
银行就在地坑旁边

386
00:20:31,450 --> 00:20:32,990
Guess that's the end of my job.
估计我的职业生涯到此为止

387
00:20:33,010 --> 00:20:36,170
Hey, I'm curious about the billboard on the bank building.
嘿 你们银行上头那广告牌是啥意思

388
00:20:36,190 --> 00:20:37,480
-Have you seen it? -How could I miss it?
-你看到了吗？ -怎么能躲得过？

389
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:40,860
And I saw the ads too, on TV.
那广告还出现在电视上

390
00:20:40,890 --> 00:20:43,210
No more ads for cars or discount furniture.
电视不再播卖车卖家具的广告了

391
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:47,610
Just, "Charles Krantz, 39 great years. Thanks, Chuck."
只播“感谢查尔斯·克兰兹39年来的峥嵘岁月 谢谢你 查克”

392
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:49,530
So, he doesn't work at the bank?
他不是你银行的人？

393
00:20:49,550 --> 00:20:52,400
He's not retiring from the bank?
他不是从你银行退休？

394
00:20:52,420 --> 00:20:55,100
I don't know Charles Krantz.
我根本不认识这个人

395
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:59,930
I think it's just a prank. Performance art.
我觉得这就是个恶搞 玩行为艺术

396
00:20:59,950 --> 00:21:01,510
Take care.
你保重

397
00:21:07,830 --> 00:21:10,510
They look like refugees.
他们看起来像是灾民

398
00:21:10,530 --> 00:21:11,710
Yeah.
是啊

399
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:16,390
No one looks that concerned.
至少大家不再惊慌失措了

400
00:21:16,410 --> 00:21:18,170
What good would that do?
那又怎样？

401
00:21:18,190 --> 00:21:20,690
All was concerned at the start.
刚开始大家都惊慌失措

402
00:21:20,710 --> 00:21:22,520
Remember the protests?
还记得那些抗议吗？

403
00:21:22,540 --> 00:21:24,390
You remember they knocked over the fence at the White House,
还记得他们推倒白宫的围栏吗？

404
00:21:24,410 --> 00:21:26,310
and all those students got shot?
记得他们向那些学生开枪吗？

405
00:21:26,330 --> 00:21:28,050
-Yeah. -And the overthrow of the Russian government.
-是的 -还有俄罗斯政府被推翻

406
00:21:28,070 --> 00:21:30,660
You got the Four Day War between Pakistan and India
巴基斯坦和印度间的四日战争

407
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:35,970
and the fucking... the volcano in Germany.
还有他妈的德国火山喷发

408
00:21:35,990 --> 00:21:39,440
There was a volcano in Germany. That's, that's crazy.
德国火山还能喷发 太扯了

409
00:21:39,470 --> 00:21:41,980
And we just kept saying, "Oh, it's gonna blow over."
我们自我安慰 一切都会过去的

410
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:45,690
That doesn't look to be happening, though, does it?
看来过不去的 对吧？

411
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:48,460
No.
是啊

412
00:21:48,480 --> 00:21:52,330
I think that suicides will slow down.
我觉得自杀的人最终会减少

413
00:21:52,350 --> 00:21:57,950
I think people will just...wait.
我觉得人们最终会等待

414
00:21:58,930 --> 00:22:01,080
For what?
等什么？

415
00:22:01,100 --> 00:22:03,150
The end.
等结局

416
00:22:04,890 --> 00:22:08,020
This is the end of everything.
万物的大结局

417
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:11,110
I mean, we're, we're going through the five stages of grief.
我们正处在悲伤模型第五阶段

418
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:16,750
{\an9}【库伯勒-罗丝悲伤模型五阶段：否认 愤怒 恳求 沮丧 接受】

419
00:22:11,110 --> 00:22:15,460
Don't you get it? I mean, we just, we just landed on the final stage.
你明白吗？我们到了最后阶段

420
00:22:15,460 --> 00:22:17,500
Acceptance.
接受

421
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:25,380
The waiting...I think that's the hardest part.
等待 才是最难熬的

422
00:22:25,740 --> 00:22:28,630
And the whole thing, it just, it-it came out of nowhere, right?
灾难不打声招呼就冒出来了

423
00:22:28,650 --> 00:22:31,290
I mean, everyone knew there was trouble with the environment.
我是说 大家早知道有自然环境问题

424
00:22:31,310 --> 00:22:34,810
I mean, I think even the right-wing nutjobs were secretly, they got it.
即便是右翼疯子也私下里心知肚明

425
00:22:34,830 --> 00:22:36,390
But this...
但现在

426
00:22:37,830 --> 00:22:39,330
this...
现在这些

427
00:22:39,530 --> 00:22:45,430
this is just 60 different varieties of shit.
现在这些不过是各种屁事的集合

428
00:22:45,450 --> 00:22:48,910
It's just so much shit that happened fast.
屁事排山倒海地来

429
00:22:48,930 --> 00:22:53,180
It's like a year, man. Fourteen months.
现在一年都十四个月了

430
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:57,040
Sucks.
倒霉啊

431
00:22:59,640 --> 00:23:03,520
Yeah. Sucks.
是啊 倒霉啊

432
00:23:07,170 --> 00:23:09,630
Skywriting.
飞机写字

433
00:23:11,610 --> 00:23:15,190
I haven't seen one of those since I was a kid.
长大后就再也没见过这种事

434
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:14,810
{\an8}谢谢你 亠亠

435
00:23:19,180 --> 00:23:22,080
What the fuck?
搞什么鬼？

436
00:23:22,110 --> 00:23:27,570
My sentiments... exactly.
我也想问同样的问题

437
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:28,710
{\an8}谢谢你 查克

438
00:23:36,290 --> 00:23:38,180
{\an8}谢谢你 查克！

439
00:23:38,830 --> 00:23:40,830
{\an8}街头艺人万岁

440
00:23:41,020 --> 00:23:43,060
{\an8}查克万岁

441
00:23:43,130 --> 00:23:44,690
{\an8}查克我爱你

442
00:23:44,730 --> 00:23:48,130
{\an8}查克yyds

443
00:23:52,010 --> 00:23:56,080
{\an8}爱你查克

444
00:24:00,700 --> 00:24:02,420
Whoa, whoa, whoa, where have you been?
喂 喂 喂  你上哪去了？

445
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:05,730
Are you kidding? I had to run here.
你不知道吗？我跑过来的

446
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:08,780
The traffic's insane, and half the cars are empty.
路全堵了 一半人把车都仍路上了

447
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:09,910
Dr. Winston's MIA.
温斯顿医生跑了

448
00:24:09,930 --> 00:24:11,600
-What? -Yeah.
-什么意思？ -你没听错

449
00:24:11,620 --> 00:24:13,950
He walked in this morning, and he looked around and he walked out again.
他今天早上过来看了一圈转头就走了

450
00:24:13,970 --> 00:24:15,480
And now I can't find him.
再也找不到他了

451
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:17,440
He dropped his pager when he walked out.
他把对讲机都扔门口了

452
00:24:17,460 --> 00:24:19,740
Okay. I'll scrub in.
好 那我来开刀

453
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:22,090
The beds are empty.
床位都空了

454
00:24:22,110 --> 00:24:25,680
Most of them walked out. I-I-I transferred the last of the stable ones.
病人基本都自己走出去了 我把最后一个扶出去的

455
00:24:25,700 --> 00:24:30,090
But, Felicia, there's something weird.
但是 菲莉西娅 有点怪事

456
00:24:31,210 --> 00:24:33,570
What is that?
怎么回事？

457
00:24:45,270 --> 00:24:47,460
What's wrong with the monitor?
机子坏了吗？

458
00:24:47,490 --> 00:24:51,410
That's the thing, it-it's, it's not just that one.
这就是怪事 不只这一台

459
00:25:14,640 --> 00:25:18,110
I don't know, Fel. I don't know.
我搞不懂 小菲 搞不懂

460
00:25:18,130 --> 00:25:22,590
I mean... I might want to get out of here.
我 我也不想待在这了

461
00:25:22,610 --> 00:25:24,850
I might wanna go home.
我想回家

462
00:25:24,870 --> 00:25:29,090
I don't think I need to be here anymore.
没必要再待在这了

463
00:25:30,340 --> 00:25:33,660
{\an8}信号中断

464
00:25:51,870 --> 00:25:56,120
{\an8}菲莉西娅

465
00:25:56,440 --> 00:25:59,190
{\an8}呼出失败 无信号

466
00:26:47,060 --> 00:26:53,170
{\an8}查尔斯·查克·克兰兹

467
00:26:53,170 --> 00:26:54,320
{\an8}查尔斯·查克·克兰兹
39个峥嵘岁月！

468
00:26:54,320 --> 00:26:58,780
{\an8}查尔斯·查克·克兰兹
39个峥嵘岁月！
谢谢你 查克！

469
00:27:11,670 --> 00:27:13,630
You okay, sir?
还好吗 老先生？

470
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:17,000
Yeah. Just taking a rest.
好 就歇歇脚

471
00:27:17,640 --> 00:27:20,880
I walked downtown to look at the sinkhole
我走去市中心看大地坑了

472
00:27:20,900 --> 00:27:22,930
and take a few pictures with my phone.
还用手机拍了几张照片

473
00:27:22,950 --> 00:27:26,280
Thought one of the local TV stations might be interested,
我以为电视台可能会想要

474
00:27:26,300 --> 00:27:30,540
but they all seem to be off the air.
但全都停播了

475
00:27:30,560 --> 00:27:33,670
Except for pictures of Krantz.
除了克兰兹的广告

476
00:27:34,570 --> 00:27:38,090
All Krantz all the time.
到处都是克兰兹啊

477
00:27:38,440 --> 00:27:41,290
-Any idea who he is? -None.
-知道他是谁吗？ -不知道

478
00:27:41,310 --> 00:27:46,650
I've asked two dozen people, at least. Nobody knows.
我问过至少二十多人 没人知道

479
00:27:46,670 --> 00:27:51,130
Our man, Krantz, is the Oz of the apocalypse.
克兰兹可是这个时代的幕后大佬啊

480
00:27:51,150 --> 00:27:53,910
Our last meme.
只闻其名 不见其身啊

481
00:27:53,930 --> 00:27:56,310
-Where are you heading? -Harvest Acres.
-你往哪走？ -丰收里

482
00:27:56,330 --> 00:27:59,610
Nice little enclave off the beaten track.
世外桃源般的小区

483
00:27:59,630 --> 00:28:02,040
I'm heading there myself.
我正要去那儿

484
00:28:02,060 --> 00:28:03,530
-My ex lives there. -Huh.
-我前妻住那儿 -噢

485
00:28:03,550 --> 00:28:04,820
Well...
好吧

486
00:28:04,900 --> 00:28:07,250
I can walk with you if you like.
要一起去吗？

487
00:28:07,270 --> 00:28:09,540
What do you do, Sam?
山姆 你做什么工作的？

488
00:28:09,560 --> 00:28:11,950
If you still do anything, I mean.
如果还有工作的话

489
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:16,420
Owner and chief undertaker for Yarborough Funeral Home.
亚伯勒殡仪馆的老板兼首席殡葬师

490
00:28:16,420 --> 00:28:17,980
Oh, man!
噢 老天

491
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:19,240
Yeah.
是啊

492
00:28:19,260 --> 00:28:21,680
We had a boom.
生意之前好到爆

493
00:28:21,700 --> 00:28:22,990
It's hard to feel good about it,
谈起这个就高兴

494
00:28:23,010 --> 00:28:26,380
but business was never better than it was a few weeks ago.
最火的还是前几周

495
00:28:27,140 --> 00:28:32,780
But my real interest's meteorology.
但我真正志向所在是气象学

496
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:36,210
Dreamed of being a television weatherman in my salad days,
年轻时我曾想当电视上天气预报员

497
00:28:36,210 --> 00:28:38,780
maybe even one of the networks.
也许能成全国台的

498
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:41,050
But n-no.
但 没成

499
00:28:41,070 --> 00:28:42,960
I keep up, though.
不过还继续关注着

500
00:28:42,980 --> 00:28:45,530
Read the journals.
读有关的书

501
00:28:45,550 --> 00:28:52,100
And I can tell you something amazing if you want to hear.
想听的话 有些我读到的奇闻异事

502
00:28:52,120 --> 00:28:57,110
You know how people say there are 24 hours in a day?
大家都说一天有24小时 对吧？

503
00:28:57,130 --> 00:28:59,040
Well, they're wrong.
其实他们错了

504
00:28:59,090 --> 00:29:06,550
There were 23 hours and 56 minutes in a stellar day.
在恒星日中一天有23小时零56分钟

505
00:29:08,410 --> 00:29:15,880
{\an8}查尔斯·查克·克兰兹
39个峥嵘岁月！
谢谢你 查克！

506
00:29:11,530 --> 00:29:13,320
Plus a few odd seconds.
还零几秒钟

507
00:29:13,530 --> 00:29:15,020
There "were"?
你说的是过去吧？

508
00:29:15,050 --> 00:29:17,160
Based on my calculations,
根据我的计算

509
00:29:17,190 --> 00:29:20,930
which I assure you I can back up, my math is good,
相信我 我的数学很好

510
00:29:21,020 --> 00:29:26,400
there are now 24 hours and two minutes in a day.
现在一天有24小时零2分钟长

511
00:29:26,420 --> 00:29:28,270
Do you know what that means?
知道这什么意思？

512
00:29:28,290 --> 00:29:30,440
Well, you're saying the Earth's rotation is slowing down?
地球自转速度在减慢？

513
00:29:30,460 --> 00:29:32,440
Exactly.
没错

514
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:37,190
Lot of folks think all of these disasters are 'cause of what we've done to the environment.
很多人将这些灾难归咎于我们破坏环境

515
00:29:37,210 --> 00:29:38,950
Not so.
并非如此

516
00:29:39,430 --> 00:29:42,630
I'm the first to admit, we treated our mother,
我先承认 我们对待母亲非常坏

517
00:29:42,650 --> 00:29:46,420
yes, she's our mother, all of us, very badly.
是的 地球母亲 万物之母

518
00:29:46,440 --> 00:29:49,680
Certainly molested her, if not outright raped her.
我们肯定玷污了她 几近强暴

519
00:29:49,700 --> 00:29:56,860
But... we're puny compared to the great clock of the universe.
但比起宇宙那浩瀚机制 我们只不过是一粒尘埃

520
00:29:56,880 --> 00:29:58,120
No.
是呀

521
00:29:58,320 --> 00:30:00,000
Whatever's happening
不论是什么原因

522
00:30:00,020 --> 00:30:03,870
is much larger than environmental degradation.
问题绝对比环境恶化更大

523
00:30:03,890 --> 00:30:06,570
The math says so.
这就是数学告诉我的

524
00:30:06,590 --> 00:30:09,530
And, and math can do a lot of things.
数学能做很多事

525
00:30:09,550 --> 00:30:16,340
I mean, math can be art... but it can't lie.
数学可以是门艺术 但数学可不会撒谎

526
00:30:16,770 --> 00:30:20,800
{\an8}丰收里小区

527
00:30:20,820 --> 00:30:25,240
You know what? I think I'll sit
你看 我要先坐会儿

528
00:30:25,260 --> 00:30:32,940
and enjoy the sunset while I wait for the arthritis to settle a bit.
边欣赏日落 边歇歇脚

529
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:36,250
You care to join me?
要一起坐会儿吗？

530
00:30:39,230 --> 00:30:41,180
I think I'll go on.
我还想继续走

531
00:30:41,490 --> 00:30:44,820
The ex. I understand.
你前妻 我理解

532
00:30:44,840 --> 00:30:50,200
Well, it was nice speaking with you, Mr. Anderson.
好的 一路顺风 安德森先生

533
00:31:30,370 --> 00:31:31,720
Hey.
你好

534
00:31:32,190 --> 00:31:33,680
Hey.
你好

535
00:31:34,070 --> 00:31:39,180
Don't worry. I'm going to see my ex-wife, Felicia Anderson.
别怕 我正去我前妻那儿 菲莉西娅·安德森

536
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:41,880
I think she's back to Gordon now.
她现在改回娘家姓戈登了

537
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:44,970
She lives on Fern Lane, number 19.
她住在费恩巷19号

538
00:31:44,990 --> 00:31:48,420
Yeah, I know Miss Gordon.
是的 我认识戈登小姐

539
00:31:48,860 --> 00:31:51,230
What are you doing out?
你大晚上出来干嘛？

540
00:31:51,610 --> 00:31:54,950
I wanted to go skating.
溜旱冰

541
00:31:55,830 --> 00:31:58,640
I used to love skating.
以前我特别喜欢溜旱冰

542
00:31:58,660 --> 00:32:01,790
Then you should go skating.
那现在就该就去溜

543
00:32:02,960 --> 00:32:04,510
Maybe I should.
也许我真该去溜

544
00:32:04,530 --> 00:32:08,600
Why do you see Miss Gordon if she's your ex?
你都跟戈登小姐分手了 咋还去见她？

545
00:32:08,620 --> 00:32:10,560
I still like her.
我还是喜欢她

546
00:32:10,580 --> 00:32:13,060
Do you fight?
你们吵架吗？

547
00:32:13,150 --> 00:32:14,960
We used to.
以前吵

548
00:32:15,940 --> 00:32:18,050
We get along better now that we're exes.
分手后 我们相处得更好了

549
00:32:18,070 --> 00:32:21,380
Miss Gordon gives us gingersnap cookies sometimes.
戈登小姐有时会来送她烤的姜饼干

550
00:32:21,410 --> 00:32:23,200
I like Oreos better, but...
我其实更喜欢奥利奥 不过...

551
00:32:23,220 --> 00:32:27,070
That's just the way the cookie crumbles, right?
就像是盒巧克力 不能每颗都合心意 对吧？

552
00:32:27,070 --> 00:32:28,640
Gingersnaps don't crumble.
姜饼干里没巧克力

553
00:32:28,640 --> 00:32:30,850
At least not until you crunch them...
除非和奥利奥一起吃...

554
00:32:40,220 --> 00:32:42,540
You better go home, I guess.
你抓紧回家吧

555
00:32:44,570 --> 00:32:47,620
It's too dark for skating without streetlights.
没路灯 天太黑 没法溜

556
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:52,230
Is everything gonna be okay?
会没事吗？

557
00:32:54,890 --> 00:32:56,880
Sure it is.
当然会

558
00:33:05,580 --> 00:33:08,130
{\an8}谢谢你 查克！

559
00:33:31,140 --> 00:33:32,920
Go home.
回家去

560
00:33:33,660 --> 00:33:36,860
Go home to your Mom and Dad.
回家去找你爸妈

561
00:33:38,150 --> 00:33:40,560
Do it now.
抓紧

562
00:34:19,410 --> 00:34:22,450
Oh, thank God. Oh, thank God.
哦 谢天谢地 谢天谢地

563
00:34:22,840 --> 00:34:26,640
-Thank God. -They, they just...
-谢天谢地 -这些都 都...

564
00:34:28,240 --> 00:34:31,090
They just, they just started showing up.
这些都突然冒出来了

565
00:34:31,110 --> 00:34:33,810
No, I know, I know, I saw.
我知道 我知道 我也看到了

566
00:34:33,900 --> 00:34:35,970
Is it just here?
只是这个小区吗？

567
00:34:35,990 --> 00:34:38,440
I think it's everywhere.
我觉得到处都有

568
00:34:39,900 --> 00:34:43,330
I think it's almost...
看起来时候到了

569
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:48,430
Yeah...
是啊

570
00:34:49,170 --> 00:34:51,860
Yeah, I think it's almost...
是的 时候到了

571
00:36:32,280 --> 00:36:35,780
It's the brightest I've ever seen the stars.
这是我见过的最亮的星空

572
00:36:40,200 --> 00:36:42,450
Just look at that.
看那里

573
00:36:44,420 --> 00:36:47,230
There's Aquila the eagle.
那是天鹰座

574
00:36:47,250 --> 00:36:48,680
Mm-hm.
嗯

575
00:36:49,210 --> 00:36:50,420
There's, uh...
那是...

576
00:36:50,860 --> 00:36:53,950
Cygnus the swan.
天鹅座

577
00:37:01,520 --> 00:37:03,750
You see it?
你看到了吗？

578
00:37:16,670 --> 00:37:18,970
And there's the North Sta...
那是北极...

579
00:37:22,330 --> 00:37:24,700
Did you just see that?
你看到刚才那个吗？

580
00:37:24,720 --> 00:37:26,340
Yeah.
看到了

581
00:37:31,420 --> 00:37:33,720
There goes Mars.
火星也没了

582
00:37:48,530 --> 00:37:51,510
I'm scared.
我好怕

583
00:37:53,450 --> 00:37:55,340
I am too.
我也是

584
00:37:55,360 --> 00:37:57,920
It's okay, honey.
没事的 亲爱的

585
00:37:59,100 --> 00:38:01,880
You go on.
你先走一步

586
00:38:02,930 --> 00:38:07,610
You go on ahead, okay?
我们到那里再重逢

587
00:38:10,900 --> 00:38:14,440
Just thirty-nine years.
活了才39年

588
00:38:20,350 --> 00:38:24,640
Thirty-nine great years.
是39个峥嵘岁月

589
00:38:30,400 --> 00:38:33,150
Thanks, Chuck.
谢谢你 查克

590
00:38:58,070 --> 00:38:59,420
I love y...
我爱...

591
00:39:13,130 --> 00:39:15,500
{\an8}第二幕

592
00:39:15,500 --> 00:39:20,690
{\an8}第二幕
街头艺人万岁

593
00:39:23,710 --> 00:39:27,410
With the help of her friend, Mac, who has an old van,
多亏她那开着旧面包车的朋友麦克帮忙

594
00:39:27,500 --> 00:39:30,820
Taylor Franck sets up her drum kit in
泰勒·弗兰克才能把架子鼓摆到

595
00:39:30,850 --> 00:39:35,110
her favored spot on the Eighth Street Promenade.
第八街长廊上她最喜欢的那个地方

596
00:39:37,110 --> 00:39:39,180
It's Thursday afternoon.
这天是周四下午

597
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:42,050
The weather is fucking gorgeous,
这天的天气 真是绝了

598
00:39:42,080 --> 00:39:46,100
and the streets are thronged with people looking forward to the weekend,
街上人来人往 大家都在幻想着周末

599
00:39:46,120 --> 00:39:49,060
which is always better than the weekend itself.
毕竟幻想总比现实好

600
00:39:49,080 --> 00:39:51,540
-All good. Taylor? -Yeah, thanks.
-泰勒 都差不多了吧？ -嗯 谢了

601
00:39:51,560 --> 00:39:54,500
Ten percent is all the thanks I want, dude.
老铁 别忘分我一成收入

602
00:39:54,610 --> 00:40:00,950
Taylor, and Mac too, work part-time at Doctor Records on Castle Street.
泰勒和麦克都在城堡街的心疗唱片店打零工

603
00:40:00,980 --> 00:40:05,150
But on a good day Taylor can make almost as much busking.
打赏多时 泰勒挣得差不多跟打零工一样

604
00:40:02,230 --> 00:40:06,340
{\an8}魔术帽
每笔打赏都会精彩翻倍

605
00:40:07,320 --> 00:40:12,810
Busk-drumming isn't what her parents saw for her when she enrolled at Juilliard,
当初考上茱莉亚时 她爸妈可没料到她会上街打鼓

606
00:40:07,380 --> 00:40:20,080
{\an9}【茱莉亚学院是世界顶尖的音乐学校】

607
00:40:12,890 --> 00:40:16,020
and they don't know yet that she dropped out.
更不知道她现在还辍了学

608
00:40:16,460 --> 00:40:19,680
Juilliard wanted you to think about what you were doing,
在茱莉亚他们教你多动脑子

609
00:40:19,770 --> 00:40:29,940
but as far as Taylor is concerned, the beat is your friend and thinking is the enemy.
在泰勒眼里 跟着鼓点走就对了 多想一下灵感就跑了

610
00:40:32,690 --> 00:40:36,410
She starts warming up, going easy at first.
她先热身 一开始节奏简单

611
00:40:36,430 --> 00:40:39,200
slow tempo, no cowbell,
节奏缓慢 不敲牛铃

612
00:40:39,400 --> 00:40:44,600
not minding that the magic hat stays empty except for her two crumpled dollars
不在乎魔术帽空着 里面只有她自己放的钱

613
00:40:44,620 --> 00:40:50,390
and a quarter flipped contemptuously by a dude on a skateboard.
还有个滑板小子随随便便丢进去的硬币

614
00:40:50,410 --> 00:40:54,210
There is time. There is a way in.
时间还早 总能找到切入点

615
00:40:54,230 --> 00:41:00,520
Finding the in is half the fun. Maybe even most of it.
找到切入点才是占最大头的乐趣

616
00:41:01,370 --> 00:41:07,270
Janice Halliday is on her way home from seven hours at Paper and Page,
珍妮丝·哈利迪在书店工作一天后正在回家

617
00:41:07,290 --> 00:41:10,450
and may walk all the way to the ocean.
大概会去海边走走

618
00:41:10,470 --> 00:41:14,100
Her boyfriend of 16 months just broke up with her,
谈了一年多的男友刚甩了她

619
00:41:14,120 --> 00:41:16,570
and he did it the modern way.
随便发个消息甩了她

620
00:41:14,170 --> 00:41:16,700
{\an7}女：怎么不回我消息了？
男：咱俩不合适 你是个好人 继续做朋友？？

621
00:41:16,570 --> 00:41:17,980
Motherfucker!
王八蛋！

622
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:25,030
It was totally unexpected, like having a door slammed in your face just as you were getting ready to walk through it.
这突如其来 犹如当头一棒把门关在脸上

623
00:41:25,050 --> 00:41:26,590
-It was... -Fucking bullshit!
-那感觉... -真他妈离谱

624
00:41:26,610 --> 00:41:28,160
...fucking bullshit.
...真他妈离谱

625
00:41:28,180 --> 00:41:32,430
She isn't in love with him. never even kidded herself that she was.
她从没动过真情 也没天真地以为自己爱过他

626
00:41:32,450 --> 00:41:34,300
-But still it... -Fucking sucks.
-但依然... -他喵的糟透了

627
00:41:34,320 --> 00:41:37,610
...is a dismaying shock just the same.
...打她个措手不及

628
00:41:37,630 --> 00:41:42,650
She supposes she'll have some wine when she gets home and cry.
她打算回家后喝点酒 顺便哭一场

629
00:41:42,670 --> 00:41:48,090
Maybe queue up one of her big band playlists and dance drunk around the room.
说不定还会播个爵士乐 在屋里醉舞一番

630
00:41:48,110 --> 00:41:50,880
She loved to dance in high school.
她读高中时就爱跳舞

631
00:41:50,900 --> 00:41:53,800
Maybe she can recapture a little of that happiness.
也许能借此重温当年那份快乐

632
00:41:53,820 --> 00:41:56,030
-Fucking really?! -Excuse me.
-去你妈的 -说什么？

633
00:41:56,050 --> 00:41:58,520
Sorry, sorry, sorry. Not you, not you.
对不起 对不起 没说你 没说你

634
00:41:59,340 --> 00:42:00,960
Fuck!
他喵的！

635
00:42:01,040 --> 00:42:03,520
Got an oat milk latte for Chuck.
查克的拿铁好了

636
00:42:01,460 --> 00:42:04,650
{\an8}查克 ^v^

637
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:06,320
Charles Krantz,
查尔斯·查克·克兰兹

638
00:42:06,790 --> 00:42:11,330
Chuck to his friends, is dressed in the armor of accountancy.
在朋友眼中 他总一身会计行头

639
00:42:11,350 --> 00:42:14,950
Gray suit, blue shirt, blue tie.
灰西装 蓝衬衣配蓝领带

640
00:42:14,970 --> 00:42:19,950
His Samuel Windsor shoes are inexpensive but sturdy.
脚上那双温莎牌皮鞋虽不贵 却耐穿

641
00:42:19,970 --> 00:42:26,220
He's here for a week-long conference titled "Banking in the 21st Century."
他来这参加个主题为“二十一世纪银行业”的研讨会

642
00:42:26,240 --> 00:42:29,960
He's been sent by his bank, Midwest Trust,
他的中西部信托银行派他来的

643
00:42:29,980 --> 00:42:31,880
all expenses paid.
全程报销

644
00:42:31,900 --> 00:42:35,750
Chuck has enjoyed the speakers and the panels.
查克对嘉宾和座谈都挺有兴趣

645
00:42:35,770 --> 00:42:37,320
He was on one panel
他上过一个座谈会

646
00:42:37,340 --> 00:42:42,370
and is scheduled to be on another before the conference ends at noon tomorrow,
明天中午大会结束前还要再参加一个

647
00:42:42,390 --> 00:42:48,760
but has no wish to spend his off-duty hours in the company of 70 other accountants.
但他可不想下班后还和那群同行混在一起

648
00:42:48,780 --> 00:42:54,120
He speaks their language, but likes to think he speaks others as well.
他精通会计的那套行话 也觉得自己能融入别的圈子

649
00:42:54,140 --> 00:42:59,940
At least he did, although some of the vocabulary is now lost.
至少曾经那么自信 如今却大不如前了

650
00:42:59,960 --> 00:43:06,000
Now, his sensible Samuel Windsor Oxfords are taking him for an afternoon walk.
现在 他穿着他温莎牌牛津鞋正在午后散步

651
00:43:06,020 --> 00:43:10,050
His life is narrower than the one he once hoped for,
现在的生活没能达到最初的设想

652
00:43:10,070 --> 00:43:12,410
but he's made peace with that.
可他已经释然了

653
00:43:12,460 --> 00:43:17,790
He understands that narrowing is the natural order of things.
他明白水往低处流是自然规律

654
00:43:17,810 --> 00:43:22,410
He has a wife, Ginny, to whom he is scrupulously faithful,
他有个忠贞不渝的妻子叫珍妮

655
00:43:22,430 --> 00:43:26,540
and an intelligent, good-humored son in middle school.
还有个聪明风趣的儿子上初中

656
00:43:26,560 --> 00:43:33,190
He also has only nine months to live, though he doesn't know that yet.
他还有九个月可活 只不过他还不知道

657
00:43:36,610 --> 00:43:43,940
Taylor has been on the job for 10 minutes now and has nothing to show for it.
泰勒已经敲了十分钟了 分文未得 毫无灵感

658
00:43:44,970 --> 00:43:48,910
She sees a Mr. Businessman type coming toward her
她看见个西装男朝她走来

659
00:43:48,930 --> 00:43:51,430
and something about him, God knows what,
不知为何 他身上有股气息

660
00:43:51,450 --> 00:43:56,520
makes Taylor want to announce his approach.
让泰勒忍不住大张旗鼓宣布他登场了

661
00:43:56,540 --> 00:44:01,060
She slips first into a reggae beat, then something slinkier.
她先用松弛的摇摆热场 又切换到更撩人的节奏

662
00:44:01,080 --> 00:44:05,400
And for the first time today, Taylor feels a spark
今天头一次 泰勒火花被点燃

663
00:44:05,420 --> 00:44:09,670
and begins to whack the cowbell on the downbeat.
便在核心鼓点上敲着牛铃

664
00:44:09,690 --> 00:44:11,100
It's pretty cool.
真带感

665
00:44:11,120 --> 00:44:17,920
The groove has arrived, and the groove is like a road you want to follow.
鼓点已经到来 那律动带你一路向前

666
00:44:17,920 --> 00:44:21,680
She could speed the beat up, get some tom in there,
她本可把节拍提快 玩点花样

667
00:44:21,700 --> 00:44:27,170
but she's watching Mr. Businessman and that seems wrong for this dude.
但此刻目光是那西装男 多此一举反而不搭

668
00:44:27,190 --> 00:44:33,690
She believes Mr. Businessman will just go on past on his way to the business hotel,
她以为那西装男只是路过 要去商务酒店

669
00:44:33,710 --> 00:44:38,870
and when he's gone, Taylor will switch to something else.
等他一走 泰勒再换节拍

670
00:44:39,890 --> 00:44:43,030
But instead of floating on by...
可他却停下脚步

671
00:47:00,950 --> 00:47:02,100
Come on.
赏个脸

672
00:47:03,470 --> 00:47:05,020
Come on, little sister.
来吧 小老妹

673
00:47:05,610 --> 00:47:06,720
Let's dance.
来跳舞吧

674
00:47:06,740 --> 00:47:08,260
Dance.
跳

675
00:47:11,610 --> 00:47:13,440
Yeah!
对了

676
00:47:13,530 --> 00:47:16,060
I'll lead you. I got you.
我带你跳 有我别怕

677
00:48:04,490 --> 00:48:05,880
Uh.
啊

678
00:48:10,630 --> 00:48:14,250
It's okay. It's my glasses. It's my glasses.
没事 眼镜的事儿 眼镜的事儿

679
00:49:54,860 --> 00:49:55,990
What are we doing?
现在该做什么？

680
00:49:56,780 --> 00:49:57,820
I don't know.
我也不知道

681
00:50:14,710 --> 00:50:16,690
No more today, folks.
大伙 今天就到这了

682
00:50:16,880 --> 00:50:18,480
No more today.
今天就到这了

683
00:50:18,840 --> 00:50:22,250
No more today. We gotta quit while we're ahead.
今天就到这了 得见好就收

684
00:50:22,910 --> 00:50:26,820
{\an8}魔术帽
每笔打赏都会精彩翻倍

685
00:50:24,540 --> 00:50:26,290
Do you need a-any help at all or...
要搭把手吗

686
00:50:26,370 --> 00:50:27,810
Here, can you, uh, take this?
好 帮把这个收起来

687
00:50:27,890 --> 00:50:29,420
-Sure. -Just, just spin the thingy here.
-好 -拧这里

688
00:50:29,500 --> 00:50:31,470
But watch out for your fingers. -It'll, it'll, it'll get 'em good.
-小心别夹手了 -会雨过天晴的

689
00:50:31,550 --> 00:50:33,300
you know what I mean?
懂了吧

690
00:50:33,370 --> 00:50:35,500
-Yeah, yeah. -To doing something else.
-好 好 -找点事散散心

691
00:50:35,600 --> 00:50:37,690
What just happened?
刚太神奇了

692
00:50:37,770 --> 00:50:39,690
That was incredible.
跳的太神了

693
00:50:39,780 --> 00:50:41,130
You dance for a living?
你们是舞蹈演员吗？

694
00:50:41,210 --> 00:50:42,870
No. Oh, no. I...
哦 不 不

695
00:50:42,950 --> 00:50:44,870
-No, I do not, sir. -What do you do for a living?
-不 不是的 -你做什么的？

696
00:50:44,960 --> 00:50:46,850
Oh, no, I think I... Did I... I didn't break it, did I?
哎呦 我好像不小心搞坏了

697
00:50:46,870 --> 00:50:49,070
I think he broke it.
这个好像坏了

698
00:50:50,310 --> 00:50:51,840
Let's hit the pond.
去喷泉吧

699
00:50:51,920 --> 00:50:54,170
We'll never find parking by the Common.
那儿没停车位

700
00:50:54,530 --> 00:50:55,570
We will today.
那也要停

701
00:50:56,920 --> 00:51:01,190
Today...is magic.
今天 就像魔术一样

702
00:51:05,670 --> 00:51:09,470
Where did you learn to dance like that?
你们在哪练的这身舞功？

703
00:51:15,160 --> 00:51:17,400
Oh, no, no, no, that's yours.
别 别 别 那是你赚的

704
00:51:17,420 --> 00:51:19,010
Nope, we split it even.
不 有福同享

705
00:51:19,030 --> 00:51:23,470
By myself, I wouldn't have made half as much if I drummed till midnight.
要我自己敲 一天也赚不了这么多

706
00:51:32,440 --> 00:51:33,610
You okay?
你没事吧？

707
00:51:35,660 --> 00:51:37,340
Yeah.
还好

708
00:51:38,920 --> 00:51:41,690
Yeah. Just one of my headaches.
就是有点头疼

709
00:51:43,360 --> 00:51:45,820
Oh, no, no, no. Come on. I don't need it. You keep it.
不了 不了 真用不着 你留着吧

710
00:51:45,840 --> 00:51:48,260
Come on, man, you earned it.
来吧 老兄 你应得的

711
00:51:48,280 --> 00:51:55,000
Buy yourself dinner. Give it away. But I'm handing it to you.
拿去吃顿饭 转手送人也行 但这钱我偏要交给你

712
00:51:57,640 --> 00:51:59,400
You could do this for a living, you know?
你们干这行都能当职业了

713
00:51:59,420 --> 00:52:01,360
I don't know about that.
我可不敢这么说

714
00:52:01,380 --> 00:52:05,300
I really think we could busk our way to fame and fortune.
我真觉得靠街头表演 我们能红 能赚大钱

715
00:52:07,780 --> 00:52:11,830
What made you stop in front of me?
你怎么会停在我面前？

716
00:52:13,040 --> 00:52:16,620
Why did you start moving?
又为什么突然跳起舞？

717
00:52:16,900 --> 00:52:23,470
He could say it was because he was thinking about his old half-assed band, The Retros,
他本可说鼓点让他想起他那不成气候的追旧青年乐队

718
00:52:23,490 --> 00:52:29,370
and how he liked to dance across the stage during instrumental breaks.
他还喜欢跟着节奏跳舞

719
00:52:29,410 --> 00:52:31,160
But that's not it.
但他没这么说

720
00:52:34,590 --> 00:52:36,760
I don't know.
我也说不清

721
00:52:39,500 --> 00:52:40,960
Taylor, we gotta roll,
泰勒 该走了

722
00:52:40,980 --> 00:52:44,450
or you're gonna end up spending your take on my parking ticket.
不然你赚的钱都得交罚单了

723
00:52:44,990 --> 00:52:48,060
So, you guys don't want a career change?
你们不考虑转行跳舞吗？

724
00:52:48,080 --> 00:52:49,970
Career change? How... I mean...
转行？

725
00:52:49,990 --> 00:52:52,280
We'll make a name for ourselves.
我们肯定能闯出名堂

726
00:52:53,390 --> 00:52:55,980
You got to get in here before you go.
别急着走 先进来一下

727
00:52:56,000 --> 00:52:58,070
-Group hug. -Oh, oh, okay.
-来个大团抱！ -哦 哦 好

728
00:52:58,090 --> 00:52:59,400
-Group hug. -Okay.
-大团抱！ -来

729
00:52:59,480 --> 00:53:00,980
Go.
快 快 快

730
00:53:01,000 --> 00:53:02,600
Come on.
来 来

731
00:53:08,880 --> 00:53:10,860
Buskers forever.
街头艺人万岁

732
00:53:10,880 --> 00:53:12,430
Yeah. Buskers forever.
好了 好了

733
00:53:12,450 --> 00:53:15,690
We gotta roll before the meter maid shows up.
得赶在贴罚单前抓紧走

734
00:53:20,940 --> 00:53:22,610
I'm so sorry.
真替你难过

735
00:53:23,070 --> 00:53:24,310
That sucks.
真倒霉

736
00:53:24,330 --> 00:53:26,290
It does suck.
这确实倒霉

737
00:53:26,940 --> 00:53:28,880
I thought he was a nice guy.
我真觉得他人还不错

738
00:53:28,900 --> 00:53:32,420
He was a pretty good lover, and we had fun and all that.
床上功夫也到位 我们在一起挺开心的

739
00:53:32,690 --> 00:53:37,370
If I can find a video of us dancing, which I'm gonna look because I bet we go viral,
我回去得找下我们跳舞的视频 估计会上热搜

740
00:53:37,390 --> 00:53:44,940
I'm gonna send it to him with a text, a text that says, "This is what you're missing."
然后转发给他 再附句“这就是你错过的缘分”

741
00:53:51,580 --> 00:53:53,680
You're gonna be fine.
你会没事的

742
00:53:55,060 --> 00:53:58,710
I don't know a lot, but I know that much.
我不是全都懂 可这件事我很清楚

743
00:54:00,410 --> 00:54:07,640
You got a bright sunbeam in front of you, and you're gonna step right into it, I can tell.
光辉就在你前面 往前迈一步乌云就消散

744
00:54:08,070 --> 00:54:09,240
But yeah.
但现在

745
00:54:11,380 --> 00:54:14,350
It sucks. Not much else to say.
真倒霉 没啥好说的

746
00:54:16,640 --> 00:54:21,020
Everything goes down the drain, and all we can say is, "That sucks."
一切都完了 我们也只剩下句真倒霉

747
00:54:21,050 --> 00:54:22,220
Yeah.
对

748
00:54:23,040 --> 00:54:26,940
Maybe we're going down the drain too.
说不定谁都躲不掉这劫

749
00:54:26,960 --> 00:54:28,640
Maybe.
说不定

750
00:54:30,660 --> 00:54:32,420
I'm this way.
我走这条路

751
00:54:34,580 --> 00:54:37,390
Uh, I'm that way.
我往那边走

752
00:54:42,240 --> 00:54:44,620
Thank you for the dance.
多谢你陪我跳舞

753
00:55:39,030 --> 00:55:42,360
As he passes the place where Taylor set up her drums,
当他走过泰勒摆鼓的地方

754
00:55:42,380 --> 00:55:46,430
those two questions recur.
那两个问题又冒了出来

755
00:55:47,300 --> 00:55:51,280
Why did he stop to listen?
为什么要停下脚步听？

756
00:55:51,300 --> 00:55:56,270
And why did he start to dance?
又为什么要跳起舞？

757
00:55:57,050 --> 00:56:00,130
He doesn't know.
他自己也想不通

758
00:56:00,310 --> 00:56:06,210
And would answers make a good thing better?
有答案能让这回忆更动人吗？

759
00:56:06,230 --> 00:56:09,910
Later, he'll lose the ability to walk,
后来 他走路都成问题

760
00:56:09,930 --> 00:56:14,740
never mind dancing with little sister on the promenade.
和那个小老妹跳舞成了个传说

761
00:56:14,760 --> 00:56:19,140
Later, he'll lose the ability to chew food.
再后来 他咀嚼都成了难题

762
00:56:19,160 --> 00:56:23,190
Later, he'll forget his wife's name.
再后来 他记不住妻子的名字

763
00:56:23,210 --> 00:56:29,150
Later, he'll lose his grip on the difference between waking and sleeping
到最后 他分不清白日黑夜

764
00:56:29,170 --> 00:56:38,160
and enter a land of pain so great he will wonder why God made the world.
陷入一种让人质疑生命意义的巨大痛苦中

765
00:56:38,180 --> 00:56:45,080
What he will remember, occasionally, is how he stopped and dropped his briefcase
但有时 他还会记得当初把公文包一丢

766
00:56:45,100 --> 00:56:49,690
and began to move his hips to the beat of the drums.
跟着鼓点起舞的感觉

767
00:56:49,710 --> 00:56:55,830
And he will think that is why God made the world.
他会觉得 这就是上帝让世界存在的意义

768
00:56:55,850 --> 00:56:57,930
Just that.
仅此而已

769
00:57:13,080 --> 00:57:14,390
{\an8}第一幕

770
00:57:14,390 --> 00:57:19,160
{\an8}第一幕
我包罗万象

771
00:57:21,050 --> 00:57:24,940
Chuck was looking forward to having a baby sister.
查克一直盼着能有个小妹妹

772
00:57:24,960 --> 00:57:28,950
Of course, he was also looking forward to having parents,
更盼着父母能赶紧回来

773
00:57:28,970 --> 00:57:37,070
but none of that worked out thanks to a patch 95 of well-hidden ice on an I-95 overpass.
谁料95号高架上结的冰让一切化为泡影

774
00:57:38,590 --> 00:57:41,130
Chuck wasn't in the car when it happened
事发时查克没在车上

775
00:57:41,150 --> 00:57:43,920
because his parents were having a dinner date
他父母去享受二人世界

776
00:57:43,940 --> 00:57:47,360
and he was being babysat by his grandparents,
那天晚上他爷爷奶奶带他

777
00:57:47,380 --> 00:57:51,270
who, at the time, he was still calling Zaydee and Bubbie.
他那会儿还叫他们阿爷阿奶

778
00:57:47,380 --> 00:57:52,860
{\an9}Zaydee和Bubbie是东欧犹太移民常用的祖父母称呼

779
00:57:51,290 --> 00:57:52,840
He was seven years old.
他那时七岁了

780
00:57:52,860 --> 00:57:54,920
Excellent job.
真赞喔

781
00:57:55,210 --> 00:58:01,070
For a year and a half, it was a house of unadulterated sadness.
一年半载 屋子里全是悲伤

782
00:58:01,090 --> 00:58:05,990
Albie and Sarah Krantz had not only lost their son and daughter-in-law...
对阿尔比和莎拉·克兰兹来说 不只是儿子和儿媳没了

783
00:58:06,010 --> 00:58:07,470
Why're you not eating?
咋不吃饭了？

784
00:58:07,490 --> 00:58:12,070
...they had lost the granddaughter who would've been born just three months later.
那本该三个月后出生的孙女也没了

785
00:58:12,090 --> 00:58:13,770
What's going on?
咋回事儿？

786
00:58:13,790 --> 00:58:16,080
The name had already been picked out...
名字都选好了...

787
00:58:16,100 --> 00:58:18,520
-Her name is Alyssa. -...Alyssa.
-她叫艾雨莎 -艾雨莎

788
00:58:18,540 --> 00:58:22,060
When Chuck said that sounded to him like rain,
查克说那名字听着像下雨时

789
00:58:22,060 --> 00:58:26,130
his mother had laughed and cried at the same time.
他妈哭笑不得

790
00:58:26,150 --> 00:58:29,430
He never forgot that.
他永远忘不了那表情

791
00:58:29,850 --> 00:58:34,800
Albie processed his grief by turning to his two absolutes,
阿尔比靠两件事来排解悲伤

792
00:58:34,820 --> 00:58:38,190
numbers and alcohol.
算账和喝酒

793
00:58:38,210 --> 00:58:43,110
Sarah, though, could find no joy in her usual pleasures.
但对莎拉来说 一切却都失去了滋味

794
00:58:43,130 --> 00:58:47,980
She loved the flavors of life, music, art, and food,
曾让她陶醉的音乐 艺术和美食

795
00:58:48,000 --> 00:58:53,500
but now, found the world quiet and gray and flavorless.
如今都索然无味

796
00:58:55,360 --> 00:58:59,860
Some of the good feelings came back into the house with time.
随着时间流逝 家里又慢慢有了些温暖

797
00:58:59,880 --> 00:59:03,480
There were a lot of takeout meals after the accident,
事故后全靠外卖度日

798
00:59:03,500 --> 00:59:08,740
but around the time Chuck turned 10, his grandma started cooking again.
但查克快十岁那年 他奶奶又重新下厨

799
00:59:08,760 --> 00:59:12,590
She liked rock-and-roll while she was cooking.
她做饭时爱放摇滚乐

800
00:59:12,610 --> 00:59:20,600
Music Chuck would've thought much too young for her, but which she clearly enjoyed.
查克肯定觉得太潮了 可她显然乐在其中

801
00:59:37,230 --> 00:59:42,440
Come on, little brother, let's dance.
来吧 小老弟 来跳舞吧

802
01:00:12,580 --> 01:00:13,790
{\an8}《西区故事》

803
01:00:16,240 --> 01:00:17,110
{\an8}《雨中曲》

804
01:00:18,600 --> 01:00:19,730
{\an8}《歌厅》

805
01:00:22,840 --> 01:00:23,980
{\an8}《爵士春秋》

806
01:00:28,390 --> 01:00:30,230
{\an8}《封面女郎》

807
01:00:33,210 --> 01:00:37,510
{\an9}【电影《封面女郎》(1944)】

808
01:00:37,540 --> 01:00:42,380
You could learn those moves, kiddo. You're a natural.
小宝 你有本事学会 你天生是跳舞的料

809
01:00:42,400 --> 01:00:43,790
Wh-Where did you learn?
你在哪学的？

810
01:00:43,810 --> 01:00:45,640
High school.
高中

811
01:00:46,070 --> 01:00:49,320
What were you like in high school?
你上高中的时候是什么样的？

812
01:00:49,340 --> 01:00:51,670
I was a kusit.
我可是个小辣妹

813
01:00:49,340 --> 01:00:51,665
{\an9}【Kusit为希伯来语】

814
01:00:51,690 --> 01:00:54,210
But don't you tell your Zaydee I said that.
千万别把我这话告诉你阿爷哦

815
01:00:54,240 --> 01:00:57,090
He's old school, that one.
他是个老古董

816
01:00:58,570 --> 01:01:01,320
Chuck never told.
查克守口如瓶

817
01:01:01,580 --> 01:01:05,870
His grandparents' house became every inch his home
他把爷爷奶奶家处处都当自己家

818
01:01:05,890 --> 01:01:11,370
with one exception. the cupola on the roof.
除了塔尖阁楼

819
01:01:12,890 --> 01:01:16,930
Chuck was forbidden to go into the cupola.
查克被严令禁止进那阁楼

820
01:01:16,930 --> 01:01:23,360
That was his grandfather's rule, and it was absolute, emphatic.
那是他爷爷的一条铁律 不容置疑

821
01:01:23,380 --> 01:01:26,750
Albie wasn't a stern man in other matters.
他爷爷阿尔比做事宽容

822
01:01:26,770 --> 01:01:30,060
He was downright gentle in most respects.
平时人挺温和的

823
01:01:30,080 --> 01:01:34,540
But on this point, he was rigid.
偏偏在这事上绝不讲情面

824
01:01:35,290 --> 01:01:39,230
Chuck asked about it, of course, and more than once.
查克可不止问过一次

825
01:01:39,260 --> 01:01:43,240
What was up there? What could you see from the high window?
那上头有什么？从高高的窗户能看到啥？

826
01:01:43,260 --> 01:01:48,310
And the big question, why was the room locked?
最重要的是 为啥老是锁着？

827
01:01:48,490 --> 01:01:49,370
Grandma said...
他奶奶说...

828
01:01:49,370 --> 01:01:51,880
Because the floor isn't safe and you might go right through it.
楼上地板不结实 一踩就会坍下去

829
01:01:51,910 --> 01:01:52,820
Grandpa said...
他爷爷说...

830
01:01:52,820 --> 01:01:56,080
There's nothing up there because of that rotten floor.
由于那烂地板 屋子里空无一物

831
01:01:56,080 --> 01:01:59,960
And the only thing you can see through the windows is the shopping center.
你往窗外瞅 也就只能看到商场

832
01:01:59,980 --> 01:02:05,390
He said that until, one night, just before Chuck's 11th birthday,
他一直这么说 直到查克十一岁生日前一晚

833
01:02:05,420 --> 01:02:09,170
when he told at least part of the truth.
他才吐出部分实情

834
01:02:08,030 --> 01:02:09,790
{\an7}The cosmic calendar
宇宙历年法

835
01:02:09,810 --> 01:02:14,540
{\an7}compresses the local history of the universe into a single year.
把宇宙的历史压缩到一本365天日历

836
01:02:14,560 --> 01:02:17,100
{\an7}If the universe began on January 1st,
从1月1日宇宙诞生算起

837
01:02:17,120 --> 01:02:20,900
{\an7}it was not until May that the Milky Way formed.
我们的银河系要到5月才出现

838
01:02:19,870 --> 01:02:22,720
Drinking is not good for secrets.
俗话说酒后吐真言

839
01:02:22,740 --> 01:02:28,160
And after the death of his son, daughter-in-law, and granddaughter-to-be,
当儿子 儿媳还有那个名字听着像下雨的

840
01:02:28,180 --> 01:02:30,880
Alyssa, who sounds like rain,
未来孙女艾雨莎全都去世后

841
01:02:30,900 --> 01:02:34,210
Albie Krantz drank a great deal.
阿尔比·克兰兹就拼命喝酒

842
01:02:33,530 --> 01:02:37,430
{\an7}Everything humans have ever done occurred in that bright speck
人类全部的历史

843
01:02:37,450 --> 01:02:41,590
{\an7}at the lower right of the cosmic calendar.
都在这本日历的最后一天

844
01:02:40,370 --> 01:02:46,960
I'll bet you could see way past the Westford Mall from the cupola.
我打赌 从阁楼往外看 能看到西福商场

845
01:02:46,980 --> 01:02:52,360
You gotta be able to see the whole town from up there, I bet.
整座小镇肯定也能看得一清二楚

846
01:02:52,380 --> 01:02:58,710
If you went up there, you might see a lot more than you wanted.
要真上去了 你看见的可不只是风景

847
01:02:58,730 --> 01:03:02,110
That's why it's locked, Chucko.
小查 这门紧锁是有原因的

848
01:03:00,990 --> 01:03:04,370
{\an7}Every month is one and a quarter billion years long.
日历里每个月代表12.5亿年

849
01:03:04,390 --> 01:03:07,910
{\an7}Each day represents 40 million years.
每一天代表4000万年

850
01:03:07,170 --> 01:03:10,210
He wanted to ask what Grandpa meant.
他想问清楚

851
01:03:10,350 --> 01:03:14,160
But the adult part of him, not there in person, no, not at 10,
尽管他才10岁

852
01:03:14,180 --> 01:03:19,070
but something that had begun to speak on rare occasions,
可脑子里的成熟声音冒出来

853
01:03:19,090 --> 01:03:26,860
told him to be quiet. Be quiet and wait.
告诉他别吭声 安静地等着

854
01:03:25,800 --> 01:03:31,220
{\an7}But all of human history would occupy an area the size of my hand.
人类的全部历史就像我手掌那么大

855
01:03:31,240 --> 01:03:36,290
{\an7}We're just beginning to trace the long and tortuous path which began with the primeval...
现在让我们回到太古时代...

856
01:03:36,380 --> 01:03:39,490
You know what style of house this is?
你知道这房子是什么风格的吗？

857
01:03:39,510 --> 01:03:41,010
Victorian.
维多利亚风格

858
01:03:41,030 --> 01:03:42,790
That's right.
没错

859
01:03:43,340 --> 01:03:49,370
And not pretend Victorian either. It was built in 1885.
可不是仿古的 1885年建的正经维多利亚式

860
01:03:49,390 --> 01:03:52,420
It's been remodeled half a dozen times since.
后来翻新过大概六次吧

861
01:03:52,440 --> 01:03:57,340
But that cupola was there from the start.
可那阁楼一直保留至今

862
01:03:57,360 --> 01:03:59,860
Been here since '71.
我七十年代初搬来

863
01:03:59,880 --> 01:04:05,310
And in all those years, I haven't been up to that damn cupola half a dozen times.
搬来至今 我上那阁楼都没到六次

864
01:04:05,330 --> 01:04:07,950
'Cause the floor is rotted?
因为地板烂了？

865
01:04:08,760 --> 01:04:11,820
'Cause it's full of ghosts.
因为闹鬼

866
01:04:12,240 --> 01:04:15,490
{\an7}...around 10:30 p.m. on December 31st.
...发生在12月31日的晚上10点30分

867
01:04:15,940 --> 01:04:18,270
-Y-You remember Scrooge? -Yeah.
-还记得圣诞述异那个故事吗？ -嗯

868
01:04:18,290 --> 01:04:19,950
That Scrooge movie we watched?
那部叫做《圣诞欢歌》的电影？

869
01:04:19,970 --> 01:04:21,270
I remember.
记得

870
01:04:21,290 --> 01:04:24,930
Do you think of that as a ghost story?
你觉得那算鬼故事吗？

871
01:04:24,950 --> 01:04:26,630
I-I-I guess so.
算吧

872
01:04:26,650 --> 01:04:30,340
Heard someone say it was a ghost story.
有人说那是鬼故事

873
01:04:31,870 --> 01:04:37,000
Christmas Yet to Come.
他吓的说“圣诞节未卜先知”

874
01:04:34,740 --> 01:04:39,620
{\an7}11:59:20, evening, last day of the...
晚上11点59分20秒...

875
01:04:39,700 --> 01:04:43,860
Jefferies boy was a month later.
杰弗里家那男孩一个月后就没了

876
01:04:43,880 --> 01:04:54,740
Henry Peterson, that took longer. Four...maybe five years on.
亨利·彼得森拖得久些 等了四五年

877
01:04:54,760 --> 01:05:02,520
And by then...I almost forgot what I saw up there.
到那时 阁楼里看到的 我几乎忘得精光

878
01:05:02,550 --> 01:05:05,400
Almost.
几乎

879
01:05:06,930 --> 01:05:11,630
Said I'd never go back up there after that.
我说过再也不上去

880
01:05:11,650 --> 01:05:18,120
And I wish I hadn't because of Sarah.
真不想上去 要不是为了莎拉

881
01:05:18,520 --> 01:05:23,510
Because of your Bubbie, Chucky.
为了你的阿奶 小查

882
01:05:23,530 --> 01:05:27,430
Your sweet Bubbie.
最疼你的阿奶

883
01:05:27,450 --> 01:05:30,340
And the bread.
都是面包

884
01:05:30,360 --> 01:05:34,940
{\an7}Every person we've ever heard of, somewhere in there...
我们听说过的所有人...

885
01:05:35,020 --> 01:05:38,880
It's the waiting, Chucko.
这就是等待 小查

886
01:05:39,110 --> 01:05:42,110
That's the hard part.
这是最难熬的

887
01:05:40,890 --> 01:05:50,160
{\an7}Everything in the history books happened here in the last 10 seconds of the cosmic calendar.
所有历史书上的事 都只发生在这本日历最后10秒钟里

888
01:05:49,180 --> 01:05:52,510
Ooh! It's getting cold out there.
呜 外面真冷

889
01:05:52,530 --> 01:05:56,160
Vera says hi. She says thanks for the soup.
维拉向大家问好 还谢我煲的汤

890
01:05:56,180 --> 01:05:59,280
She laid the gossip on me, laid it good.
她把八卦全抖给我 抖得可带劲了

891
01:05:59,300 --> 01:06:02,350
Of course...That's why we have a Vera, isn't it?
当然 要不然咱咋离不开她呢

892
01:06:02,370 --> 01:06:04,380
So, what's the latest?
有什么新鲜事吗？

893
01:06:04,400 --> 01:06:09,730
Well, I don't know if you've heard, but Trish is saying Karen and Matty are in therapy.
知道吗 凯伦和马蒂在搞婚姻咨询

894
01:06:09,750 --> 01:06:15,970
-Again. -Who's Henry Peterson, Zaydee?
-搞什么？ -阿爷 亨利·彼得森到底是谁？

895
01:06:12,140 --> 01:06:18,000
{\an7}...the universe that made us or we can squander our 15 billion-year heritage.
...珍惜我们的宇宙 不要辜负这150亿年

896
01:06:18,020 --> 01:06:20,080
And get some pancake mix.
再买点煎饼粉

897
01:06:20,110 --> 01:06:22,770
Yellow box, not the orange box. You got all that?
要黄盒的 别买橙盒的 都记住了吗？

898
01:06:22,800 --> 01:06:24,180
I got it.
记住了

899
01:06:24,200 --> 01:06:26,960
-Do you need me to write it down? -I got it.
-要我写下来吗？ -我记得住

900
01:06:26,980 --> 01:06:30,300
Don't you think about driving. The walk will sober you up.
别开车 走路去能醒醒酒

901
01:06:30,330 --> 01:06:32,780
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
好 好 好

902
01:06:49,740 --> 01:06:52,470
He'll be back with some groceries.
他去便利店了 一会儿就回来

903
01:06:52,490 --> 01:06:58,340
Then, how about tonight, we do some s'mores in the fireplace?
要不今晚一起烤棉花糖？

904
01:06:58,360 --> 01:06:59,570
Yeah.
随便

905
01:06:59,600 --> 01:07:02,010
Yeah.
好吧

906
01:07:02,370 --> 01:07:06,050
Was he blabbing to you about his ghosts?
他是不是跟你说闹鬼的事了？

907
01:07:06,080 --> 01:07:09,550
The ones that live in the cupola?
阁楼里闹鬼的事？

908
01:07:09,900 --> 01:07:11,490
Yeah.
是呀

909
01:07:11,640 --> 01:07:14,700
Well, are there?
是真的吗？

910
01:07:15,070 --> 01:07:17,400
What do you think?
你说呢？

911
01:07:17,420 --> 01:07:20,060
I wouldn't pay too much attention to Zaydee.
别太信你阿爷

912
01:07:20,080 --> 01:07:26,600
He's a good man. But, sometimes, well, sometimes, he drinks too much.
他人不错 就是有时喝得太多

913
01:07:26,630 --> 01:07:29,770
Then he rides his hobby horses. I'm sure you know what I'm talking about.
喝多了就会天马行空 你懂他那一套

914
01:07:29,800 --> 01:07:33,730
Who was the Jefferies boy?
杰弗里家男孩是谁？

915
01:07:36,400 --> 01:07:41,110
Well...that was a very sad thing, kiddo.
好吧 小宝 那是件让人心酸的事

916
01:07:41,370 --> 01:07:43,780
He lived on the next block over,
他住旁边那巷子

917
01:07:43,800 --> 01:07:49,310
and he got hit by a car when he chased a ball into the street.
追球追到马路上结果被车撞了

918
01:07:49,330 --> 01:07:52,810
It happened a long time ago.
那是很久前的事儿了

919
01:07:53,680 --> 01:08:00,800
And if your grandpa says he saw it before it happened, he's mistaken.
要是你爷爷说他提前见过那一幕 他并没有

920
01:08:02,380 --> 01:08:06,800
He just drinks too much.
那只是他酒后乱说

921
01:08:15,610 --> 01:08:20,290
You know, I could take those to Mrs. Stanley if you want.
要不我帮你送到史坦利奶奶那儿？

922
01:08:20,310 --> 01:08:24,900
Oh, that's very thoughtful of you. I bet Vera'd love that.
哎呀 你真贴心 维拉看到你肯定特开心

923
01:08:26,890 --> 01:08:28,480
Just wonderful.
简直绝了

924
01:08:28,500 --> 01:08:30,510
Your, your grandmother is an artist.
你奶奶真是个烘焙大师

925
01:08:30,540 --> 01:08:33,310
Thank you for bringing them over. Was that your idea?
谢谢你带来 你主动要来送的吧？

926
01:08:33,330 --> 01:08:35,050
-Be honest. -It was.
-说实话哦 -是的

927
01:08:35,070 --> 01:08:37,700
Well, can I make you a cup of tea?
要喝茶吗？

928
01:08:37,720 --> 01:08:42,390
Um, I don't drink tea, but, um, I wouldn't mind a glass of milk.
其实我不喝茶 有杯牛奶就完美了

929
01:08:43,670 --> 01:08:46,100
Well, your grandmother's a saint.
你奶奶真是个大好人

930
01:08:46,130 --> 01:08:47,470
And what about your granddad?
你爷爷呢？

931
01:08:47,470 --> 01:08:49,650
Did he have that thing on his back looked at?
他背上那东西去检查了吗？

932
01:08:49,680 --> 01:08:52,150
Yeah, the, the doctor took it off and had it tested.
嗯 医生拿掉了 还做了化验

933
01:08:52,170 --> 01:08:53,850
Tell me everything.
全告诉我

934
01:08:53,870 --> 01:08:56,550
It wasn't one of the bad ones.
不是坏的那种

935
01:08:56,570 --> 01:08:58,290
Thank God for that.
谢天谢地

936
01:08:58,310 --> 01:08:59,780
Yeah.
嗯

937
01:09:00,880 --> 01:09:07,600
He, um, he was talking to Grandma about someone named Henry Peterson.
他跟奶奶聊那个叫亨利·彼得森的人

938
01:09:07,620 --> 01:09:08,910
So awful.
太惨了

939
01:09:08,930 --> 01:09:12,350
You know, Henry was a bookkeeper, just like your granddad.
亨利跟你爷爷一样是管账的

940
01:09:12,370 --> 01:09:15,750
He did a lot of the other businesses in town. The ones that your Zaydee didn't do...
还接了镇上你阿爷扛不下的活儿...

941
01:09:15,780 --> 01:09:18,170
How did it happen?
到底怎么回事？

942
01:09:19,690 --> 01:09:21,750
I don't think you want to hear about that stuff.
这种事你还是别听了

943
01:09:21,770 --> 01:09:26,550
Um, w-w-well, Granddad said it was, uh, peaceful.
呃 爷爷说 说那很平和

944
01:09:26,570 --> 01:09:28,270
Peaceful?
平和？

945
01:09:28,290 --> 01:09:31,190
He killed himself. Hung himself.
他自尽了 上吊的

946
01:09:31,210 --> 01:09:34,890
His wife, you see, she ran off with this younger man, barely old enough to vote.
他老婆跟个刚满十八的小伙子私奔了

947
01:09:34,910 --> 01:09:38,460
And she was in her 40s. What do you think of that?
她自己都四十多了 你怎么看？

948
01:09:38,480 --> 01:09:40,030
-Wow. -Damn right, wow.
-天哪 -对 可不是

949
01:09:40,050 --> 01:09:43,880
And then, I heard that...
我还听说...

950
01:09:48,020 --> 01:09:51,180
What's happening at school?
学校那边有什么新鲜事？

951
01:09:51,200 --> 01:09:53,470
Who's smooching who?
谁和谁在亲亲啦？

952
01:09:53,500 --> 01:09:58,780
"Talk honestly, for no one else hears you and I stay only a minute longer."
放心说吧 无人能闻得见 我只多留片刻

953
01:09:58,800 --> 01:10:01,790
"Do I contradict myself?
我是否自相矛盾？

954
01:10:01,810 --> 01:10:06,570
"Very well then, I contradict myself,"
好吧 那我就自相矛盾

955
01:10:06,590 --> 01:10:11,010
"I am large. I contain multitudes."
我心疆无限 我包罗万象

956
01:10:11,030 --> 01:10:13,320
On the last day of sixth grade,
六年级的最后一堂课上

957
01:10:13,340 --> 01:10:19,540
Miss Richards, a sweet, hippie-dippyish young woman who had no command of discipline
那位小清新气息 管不住课堂的理查兹老师

958
01:10:19,560 --> 01:10:24,420
and would probably not last long in the public education system,
怕是很快就要被劝退

959
01:10:24,440 --> 01:10:32,770
tried to recite for Chuck's class some verse of Walt Whitman's "Song of Myself."
还是在查克班上照念惠特曼《自我之歌》的诗

960
01:10:32,790 --> 01:10:36,260
"Failing to fetch me at first keep encouraged.
若最初寻我不得 莫失信心

961
01:10:36,280 --> 01:10:40,440
Missing me one place, search another."
错过此处 再觅它方

962
01:10:52,330 --> 01:10:55,140
That went well, don't you think?
这节课还算顺利 对吧？

963
01:10:55,160 --> 01:10:58,830
Yeah, I'm, I'm sorry about that.
嗯 让您为难了

964
01:10:59,390 --> 01:11:09,380
What does he mean when he says, "I am large, I contain multitudes"?
惠特曼那句“我心疆无限 我包罗万象”是啥意思？

965
01:11:09,400 --> 01:11:11,730
What do you think he means?
你觉得他想表达什么？

966
01:11:11,750 --> 01:11:14,090
All the people he knows.
包罗他认识的所有人

967
01:11:14,110 --> 01:11:15,520
Yes.
对

968
01:11:15,880 --> 01:11:19,050
But maybe he means even more.
但也许不止于此

969
01:11:19,080 --> 01:11:22,870
Here. Come here.
来 过来

970
01:11:24,320 --> 01:11:26,780
What's in there? Between my hands?
我的两手之间 那里有什么？

971
01:11:26,810 --> 01:11:28,570
My brain.
我头

972
01:11:28,590 --> 01:11:31,790
No, um, that's not exactly what I mean.
不 不是这个意思

973
01:11:31,810 --> 01:11:37,010
What's in there? Right between my hands right now.
我是说 在我两手之间 里面装的是什么

974
01:11:37,030 --> 01:11:38,180
I don't know.
我不知道

975
01:11:38,200 --> 01:11:41,260
All the people you know?
里面有你认识的所有人吗？

976
01:11:41,280 --> 01:11:42,800
I guess.
有吧

977
01:11:42,820 --> 01:11:46,780
Just the people you know?
就只有你认识的人吗？

978
01:11:46,800 --> 01:11:51,460
Everything you see. Everything you know.
里面是你见过的记住的一切

979
01:11:51,480 --> 01:11:53,570
The world, Chuck.
是整个世界 查克

980
01:11:53,590 --> 01:11:56,290
Planes in the sky. Manhole covers in the street.
天上的飞机 地上的井盖

981
01:11:56,310 --> 01:11:59,430
Every year that you live, that world inside your head
年复一年 你脑海中的世界

982
01:11:59,450 --> 01:12:04,130
will get bigger and brighter and more detailed and complex.
会越来越大 越鲜明 越丰富 越复杂

983
01:12:04,150 --> 01:12:07,780
You will build cities and countries and continents,
你会在脑海中构建城市 国家 大陆

984
01:12:07,800 --> 01:12:12,650
and you will fill them with people and faces, real and imagined.
并用真实和想象的人去充实那里

985
01:12:12,670 --> 01:12:15,070
Do you understand?
明白了吗？

986
01:12:15,090 --> 01:12:16,790
Don't stop there.
别就此止步

987
01:12:16,810 --> 01:12:21,240
You fill the whole thing with everyone you ever meet,
把你见过的 认识的

988
01:12:21,270 --> 01:12:26,750
everyone you ever know, everyone you ever just imagine.
甚至想象的每个人都给装进去

989
01:12:26,780 --> 01:12:29,760
It'll be a universe.
它就变成了个小宇宙

990
01:12:29,780 --> 01:12:35,330
A whole universe right between my hands.
整个宇宙就在我两手之间

991
01:12:35,350 --> 01:12:40,850
You contain multitudes.
你能包罗万象

992
01:12:41,180 --> 01:12:42,960
So...
那

993
01:12:44,010 --> 01:12:48,260
what happens to that universe if someone...
那个宇宙会怎样 要是有人

994
01:12:48,280 --> 01:12:50,440
I don't know,
比如说

995
01:12:50,460 --> 01:12:56,790
hits a patch of ice and goes off an overpass or...
在冰面上打滑 冲下高架桥 或者

996
01:12:56,940 --> 01:12:59,790
Don't worry too much about those things.
别太纠结这些

997
01:12:59,810 --> 01:13:05,320
Just remember that you contain multitudes, Chuck.
只要记住 你包罗万象 查克

998
01:13:05,340 --> 01:13:08,770
Isn't that wonderful?
这多棒啊

999
01:13:09,170 --> 01:13:11,450
Now, go on. You were such a good boy.
好了 就这样 你真是个好孩子

1000
01:13:11,480 --> 01:13:15,410
I've really enjoyed having you in class.
能教你我很开心

1001
01:13:35,150 --> 01:13:39,440
Chuck did enjoy his summer until August,
查克暑假本来过得挺好 直到八月

1002
01:13:39,460 --> 01:13:42,690
when Bubbie died.
他阿奶去世了

1003
01:13:45,400 --> 01:13:48,400
It happened at the grocery store down the street,
事情发生在街角的便利店里

1004
01:13:48,430 --> 01:13:52,150
in public, which was a little undignified,
公开场合 有点不太体面

1005
01:13:52,170 --> 01:13:56,250
but at least it was the kind of death where people can safely say...
至少这种死法能让人安心地说...

1006
01:13:56,280 --> 01:13:59,070
Thank God she didn't suffer.
幸好她一生没受什么罪

1007
01:13:59,090 --> 01:14:00,560
The other standby...
至于那句...

1008
01:14:00,580 --> 01:14:02,390
She had a long, full life.
她一生又长又圆满

1009
01:14:02,410 --> 01:14:05,160
...was more of a gray area.
就说不准了

1010
01:14:05,180 --> 01:14:09,620
Sarah Krantz had yet to reach her mid-60s.
毕竟她才六十多岁

1011
01:14:12,030 --> 01:14:18,720
Once more, the house on Pilchard Street was one of unadulterated sadness.
又一次 家里再次陷入彻底的悲伤

1012
01:14:19,110 --> 01:14:22,800
Albie wore his mourning band, and lost weight,
阿尔比戴上了黑纱 越发消瘦

1013
01:14:22,830 --> 01:14:25,220
and stopped telling his jokes
也不再讲笑话了

1014
01:14:25,240 --> 01:14:29,930
and began to look older than his 70 years.
比他实际七十岁还显老

1015
01:14:36,350 --> 01:14:39,370
-That's it? -Yeah.
-就买这点？ -嗯

1016
01:14:39,390 --> 01:14:41,980
Buck 75.
一块七毛五

1017
01:14:43,390 --> 01:14:50,340
Um, that lady who was in here a few weeks ago, the one who died.
几周前来的那个女士 就是后来去世的那位

1018
01:14:50,360 --> 01:14:53,780
Where was she when it happened?
事情发生在哪儿？

1019
01:14:53,800 --> 01:14:57,380
That's a little creepy, kid.
小朋友 这话题有点吓人

1020
01:14:57,410 --> 01:15:00,430
She was my grandma.
她是我奶奶

1021
01:15:01,020 --> 01:15:03,060
She was getting a loaf of bread.
她当时想拿面包

1022
01:15:03,080 --> 01:15:07,620
Pulled down almost everything on the shelf when she collapsed.
结果把整排货架都拽倒砸她身上了

1023
01:15:07,640 --> 01:15:12,250
I'm sorry if that's too much information.
要是我说多了 你别介意

1024
01:15:12,770 --> 01:15:14,630
Nah.
没事

1025
01:15:15,510 --> 01:15:18,720
I already knew that.
我早知道了

1026
01:16:12,440 --> 01:16:15,160
-No! -What?!
-别！ -啥？

1027
01:16:15,180 --> 01:16:20,830
-Get away from there! You get away from there. -What? Hey, hey!
-走开 快走开 -等下

1028
01:16:42,090 --> 01:16:45,070
Give me that.
